      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T17:40:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "hmm, this decompresses data in place, that\u0027s read a chunk, decompress it and write it back where we read it.\nhttps://godoc.org/github.com/klauspost/compress/zstd#Decoder.DecodeAll\ndoesn\u0027t say that this is supported.\nI don\u0027t see how it can be guarnateed: when we decompress, the size of decompressed data is larger, so if we write it back, eventually we will start overwriting the to-be-decompressed data.\n\nI think we need to decompress to a buffer.\nConsider adding a buffer field to Query and make this func a method of Query.",
